==English==

===Pronunciation===
*nŏt, /nɒt/, /<tt>nQt</tt>/

===Homophones===
*[[not]]
*[[naught]] ''(some dialects)''

===Noun===
'''knot''' (''plural'' '''[[knots]]''')

# A [[loop]]ing of a piece of string or of any other long, flexible material that cannot be untangled without passing one or both ends of the material through its loops.
# (''of hair, etc'') A [[tangle]]d [[clump]].
# A maze-like pattern.
# (''mathematics'') A [[closed]] [[curve]] that is an abstraction of a knot (in sense 1 above).
# A difficult situation.
#:''I got into a '''knot'''.''
# A unit of speed, equal to one [[nautical mile]] per [[hour]].
# Either of two species of small [[wading bird]], ''Calidris canutus'' and ''Calidris tenuirostris''.

